What are you doing?

5
00:00:46,068 --> 00:00:50,454
I was trying to find
a nice way to wake you up.

6
00:00:50,456 --> 00:00:52,539
Well, kudos, you found one.

7
00:00:52,541 --> 00:00:55,826
Here. Merry day
before Christmas.

8
00:00:55,828 --> 00:00:58,161
I thought we agreed not
to exchange presents.

9
00:00:58,163 --> 00:01:01,715
Well, you gave me a pretty
nice present last night.

10
00:01:01,717 --> 00:01:03,083
Actually two.

11
00:01:03,085 --> 00:01:05,419
You're terrible.

12
00:01:05,421 --> 00:01:06,887
Open it.

13
00:01:11,259 --> 00:01:15,979
Dare I say it?
Key to your heart?

14
00:01:15,981 --> 00:01:17,898
Better. It's a key
to my house.

15
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:21,985
Walden, I can't accept
a key to your house.

16
00:01:21,987 --> 00:01:24,154
It's a bit premature.

17
00:01:24,156 --> 00:01:26,440
Well, if anything in our
relationship's going to be premature,

18
00:01:26,442 --> 00:01:28,325
I prefer it to be
the house key.

19
00:01:28,327 --> 00:01:31,728
It's a very sweet gesture.

20
00:01:33,748 --> 00:01:35,115
Mistletoe.

21
00:01:36,834 --> 00:01:38,118
Oh, my!

22
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:40,320
I've got to pick up my daughter
from her father's

23
00:01:40,322 --> 00:01:43,173
and I've got to get to the
airport to pick up my parents.

24
00:01:43,175 --> 00:01:45,008
Are you sure I can't
come with you?

25
00:01:45,010 --> 00:01:46,043
Positive.

26
00:01:46,045 --> 00:01:48,095
Why not?
We get along great.

27
00:01:48,097 --> 00:01:50,514
Your parents are in town,
my mom's coming to visit.

28
00:01:50,516 --> 00:01:51,798
It's Christmas.

29
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,267
What better time for everybody
to get to know each other?

30
00:01:54,269 --> 00:01:56,770
Walden, we're still
getting to know each other.

31
00:01:56,772 --> 00:01:59,306
- I know you.
- Really?

32
00:01:59,308 --> 00:02:01,525
What color
are my eyes then?

33
00:02:01,527 --> 00:02:04,061
Brown. The left one's got a
little fleck of green in it.

34
00:02:04,063 --> 00:02:06,146
Damn.

35
00:02:06,148 --> 00:02:10,317
You say you're a size two,
but you're actually a size four.

36
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:11,935
You run the water
in the bathroom

37
00:02:11,937 --> 00:02:15,455
to cover the sound
of you peeing.

38
00:02:15,457 --> 00:02:18,608
All right fine. Let me put it
another way.

39
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:20,410
No families this year.

40
00:02:20,412 --> 00:02:23,547
And I am a size two.

41
00:02:24,382 --> 00:02:26,299
Merry Christmas.

