so figure... three hours.

72
00:03:59,343 --> 00:04:02,011
Yeah, I can't wait
to see you, too.

73
00:04:02,013 --> 00:04:04,046
So I'm thinking that since

74
00:04:04,048 --> 00:04:06,048
this is our first Christmas
without Charlie,

75
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:07,499
we should spend it together.

76
00:04:07,501 --> 00:04:11,837
Yes, Mom,
I'd rather get laid, too...

77
00:04:11,839 --> 00:04:14,273
but I think
family is more important.

78
00:04:14,275 --> 00:04:15,524
Hey, Mom.

79
00:04:15,526 --> 00:04:18,110
Yeah, I'm just driving
to Dad's.

80
00:04:18,112 --> 00:04:22,848
In 500 feet,
turn left.

81
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:26,352
Yes, I'm seeing someone.

82
00:04:26,354 --> 00:04:28,321
No, you can't meet her.

83
00:04:28,323 --> 00:04:30,907
Because it's too soon.

84
00:04:30,909 --> 00:04:32,074
I don't know what it means.

85
00:04:32,076 --> 00:04:34,076
It's just
what she keeps telling me.

86
00:04:34,078 --> 00:04:35,578
Uh, Mom, y-you're breaking up.

87
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:37,797
I-I'm sorry, what did you say?

88
00:04:38,632 --> 00:04:41,801
Y-Y-You want a tuna sandwich?

89
00:04:41,803 --> 00:04:46,038
Oh, oh, you're
in a two-man sandwich.

90
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:50,977
Uh, well, I, I hope
they're using condiments.

91
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:54,146
Uh, well, listen, I-I-I got
to go, I got another call.

92
00:04:54,148 --> 00:04:55,982
Dear Lord.

93
00:04:55,984 --> 00:04:57,350
Hello.

94
00:04:57,352 --> 00:04:59,235
Oh, Jake, merry Christmas.

95
00:04:59,237 --> 00:05:00,519
Hey, Dad,
I just wanted to call

96
00:05:00,521 --> 00:05:03,072
